Sentencas: The impedance responses and current-overpotential characteristics were studied for oxygen reducing cathodes, stoichiometric La1-xSrxMnO3 (x = 0.16-0.20) in solid oxide fuel cells, under varying conditions of temperature (700-900 degrees C) and oxygen partial pressure (1-10(-4) atm) for two distinctly different electrode morphologies (porous and dense structure).
Titulo: A study on the La1-xSrxMnO3 oxygen cathode

Sentencas: An electrode densified at the interface with the yttria-stabilized zirconia solid electrolyte was more efficient in this study.
Titulo: A study on the La1-xSrxMnO3 oxygen cathode

Sentencas: The reaction at the finely porous LSM proceeds via the triple phase boundary and ineffectively uses the mixed conductivity property of the material.
Titulo: A study on the La1-xSrxMnO3 oxygen cathode

Sentencas: Reaction mechanisms for both cases (porous and dense structure) are discussed and compared with the literature.
Titulo: A study on the La1-xSrxMnO3 oxygen cathode

Sentencas: A new, two-layered cathode structure is proposed.
Titulo: A study on the La1-xSrxMnO3 oxygen cathode
